     Dog Grooming Website Plan
Your Name: Ozzy Birge
Name of the Dog Grooming Business: Pampered Paws Grooming Studio

Ideas for your website
Idea 1: Display a portfolio of before-and-after photos of groomed dogs to showcase the quality of work and build trust with potential customers.

Idea 2: Create an online booking/appointment system that allows customers to schedule grooming services directly from the website.

Idea 3: Include detailed service descriptions and pricing information (bath, haircut, nail trim, de-shedding, specialty cuts, etc.) with package deals.

Idea 4: Feature staff profiles with credentials and experience to establish credibility and help customers feel confident leaving their pets.

Idea 5: Include customer testimonials and reviews section to build social proof and attract new clients.

Website Plan
Topic	Questions	Answers
Purpose of Website	What is the purpose and goal of the website?	The website's primary purpose is to attract dog owners seeking professional grooming services and generate new business leads. Secondary goals are to provide service information, pricing, and appointment scheduling, and to establish credibility and build trust through portfolio imagery and customer testimonials.
Target Audience	Describe the target audience (age, gender, demographics)	Primary audience: Pet owners aged 30-65 who value pet care and have disposable income for professional grooming. Secondary audience: Young professionals aged 25-35 with pets and busy schedules. Geographic focus: Local community within 5-mile radius. Demographics: Middle to upper-middle class households with one or more dogs.
Graphics	What graphics will you use on the website?	Professional photography of groomed dogs (before/after), staff at work, grooming facility interior, happy clients with pets, dog breed examples, grooming tool icons for different services, and branded logo imagery.
Color	What colors will you use within the site to enhance the purpose and brand?	Primary color: Warm blue (#2E7D9E) for trust and calm; Secondary: Peachy-orange (#E8A87C) for warmth and approachability; Accent: Cream (#F5F1E8) for backgrounds; Text: Dark gray (#333333) for readability. These colors convey professionalism while remaining welcoming and pet-friendly.
Accessibility	How will the website accommodate people with disabilities?	Include alt text for all images describing the content. Use sufficient color contrast (WCAG AA standards). Implement keyboard navigation and screen reader compatibility. Provide text alternatives for video content. Use clear, readable fonts with adequate sizing and spacing. Include descriptive link text and logical heading hierarchy.
Project Timeline	Identify the project timeline	Week 1-2: Planning, content gathering, photography; Week 3: Design mockups and approval; Week 4-5: Website development and testing; Week 6: Final revisions and launch (6-week timeline).          